  "text": "The main observation of Ref. [CITATION_1] was that this correlation offers an alternative, fully inclusive and model-independent, method of estimating the mass scale M p of the parent particles, even when some of their decay products are invisible and not seen in the detector. Unfortunately, the \"no UE\" limit of eq. (4.5) is unphysical, and the corresponding \u221a s (cal) min distribution (blue histogram in in Fig. 3 ) is unobservable. What is worse, when one tries to measure the \u221a s",
